AVP Aarakshan Virodhi Party (आरक्षण विरोधी पार्टी) is a registered political party in India. The party was registered by the Election Commission of India before the Indian general election, 2014. Sri Sanjay Sharma is National president of AVP. Party is extending its agenda over all part of the country. The main agenda of AVP to removal caste based reservation from Constitution of India and to provide equal opportunity to every citizen of country.

Suman Shekhar is National chief speaker as well as National Secretary of IT cell of AVP. Party has more than 50 Lakh antireservation supporter from different part of the country.

Party is strengthening its supporter mainly in Bihar and UP.
